ðŸ’» Here's a recap of what I learned on my Day 1 of DevSecOps :- 

1. Installed Git using yum and dnf package managers:
   - yum install git
   - dnf install git
   - sudo dnf install git
   - sudo yum install git

2. Cloned a repository and explored directories:
   - git clone https://github.com/krishnaacharyaa/wanderlust.git
   - cd wanderlust
   - ls

3. Experimented with file attributes using chattr:
   - Set immutable attribute on a file or directory:
     - chattr +i frontend
   - Removed immutable attribute:
     - chattr -i frontend

4. Explored other file operations:
   - Created files:
     - touch testfile
     - touch testtfile
   - Removed a directory and its contents:
     - rm -r file1

